   version   stable 1.2.0 1.0.12
   version unstable 1.1.8
   require binutils libglade
      opts --disable-kernel-module
  category development
 attribute x11
    source   stable http://www.daimi.au.dk/~sandmann/sysprof/sysprof-$VERSION.tar.gz
    source unstable http://www.daimi.au.dk/~sandmann/sysprof/sysprof-$VERSION.tar.gz
      info last 20120922
      info home http://www.daimi.au.dk/~sandmann/sysprof/
      desc 'sampling CPU profiler that uses a Linux kernel module
It can profile that entire system and not just a single application.
It handles shared libraries, and applications do not need to be recompiled.
It profiles all running processes, not just a single application,
has a nice graphical interface, shows the time spent in each branch
of the call tree, can load and save profiles, and is easy to use.

Sysprof requires a kernel with profiling support compiled in.'

build_old(){
rm -f configure
autoreconf -i
automake   -afc
default_build
}
